<section class="py-16 bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">Artificial Turf FAQ</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <details class="group bg-green-50 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer">
          <span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">How long does artificial turf last?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Quality artificial turf typically lasts 15–20 years with minimal maintenance. UV-stabilized products hold their color even in the Las Cruces sun. The base prep is what determines longevity — a properly compacted, well-drained base means the turf stays flat and drains right for the life of the product.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="group bg-green-50 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer">
          <span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">Does it get hot in the summer?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Artificial turf does absorb heat in direct sun — it can get warm underfoot on a 100°F afternoon, similar to a pool deck. A quick rinse with a hose cools it down instantly. Many homeowners pair turf with shade structures or trees to keep play areas comfortable in peak summer.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="group bg-green-50 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer">
          <span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">How does it drain during monsoons?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The turf itself is permeable — water passes right through. The key is the base underneath. We build a crushed rock base with proper grading so water drains away from your foundation, not toward it. Even heavy monsoon bursts drain quickly.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="group bg-green-50 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer">
          <span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">Can I combine turf with xeriscape?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">This is one of our most popular combinations. A patch of turf for the kids or dogs, surrounded by xeriscape with native plants and rock. You get the green lawn look where you want it and low-water landscaping everywhere else.</div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

